`inner ℝ (pbar.rotM₂' pbar.outerParams) (pc.w) = inner ℝ (pbar.rotM₂φ P) (pc.w)`

We need to show that `pbar.rotM₂' pbar.outerParams = pbar.rotM₂φ P`.
Looking at the definition of `pbar.rotM₂'`, it is indeed `pbar.rotM₂φ P`.

```tactics
have h4 : pbar.rotM₂' pbar.outerParams = pbar.rotM₂φ P := by
  simp [pbar.rotM₂', pbar.rotM₂]
  <;> ring_nf <;> simp [Matrix.cons_val_zero, Matrix.cons_val, Matrix.head_cons]
  <;> ring
```

Finally, we can use `h4` to complete the proof.

```tactics
rw [h4]
all_goals ring_nf <;> simp [Matrix.cons_val_zero, Matrix.cons_val, Matrix.head_cons]
<;> ring
```

The complete proof for `partials_helper4` is:
```tactics
lemma partials_helper4 {pbar : Pose} {ε : ℝ} {poly : GoodPoly}
    (pc : GlobalTheoremPrecondition poly pbar ε) (P : ℝ³) :
    ‖P‖ * nth_partial 1 (GlobalTheoremPrecondition.fu_outer P pc) pbar.outerParams =
    inner ℝ (pbar.rotM₂φ P) (pc.w) := by
  have h1 : (GlobalTheoremPrecondition.fu_outer P pc) = fun x => ‖P‖⁻¹ * inner ℝ (pbar.rotM₂ x) (pc.w) := by
    funext x
    simp [GlobalTheoremPrecondition.fu_outer]
    <;> ring_nf <;> simp [Matrix.cons_val_zero, Matrix.cons_val, Matrix.head_cons]
    <;> ring
  have h2 : nth_partial 1 (fun x => ‖P‖⁻¹ * inner ℝ (pbar.rotM₂ x) (pc.w)) pbar.outerParams =
      ‖P‖⁻¹ * (deriv (fun x => inner ℝ (pbar.rotM₂ x) (pc.w)) pbar.outerParams) 1 := by
    simp [nth_partial]
    <;> ring_nf <;> simp [Matrix.cons_val_zero, Matrix.cons_val, Matrix.head_cons]
    <;> ring
  have h3 : deriv (fun x => inner ℝ (pbar.rotM₂ x) (pc.w)) pbar.outerParams 1 =
      inner ℝ (pbar.rotM₂' pbar.outerParams) (pc.w) := by
    simp [deriv_inner, pbar.rotM₂', pbar.rotM₂]
    all_goals
      try { ring_nf <;> simp [Matrix.cons_val_zero, Matrix.cons_val, Matrix.head_cons] }
      <;> try { tauto }
  have h4 : pbar.rotM₂' pbar.outerParams = pbar.rotM₂φ P := by
    simp [pbar.rotM₂', pbar.rotM₂]
    <;> ring_nf <;> simp [Matrix.cons_val_zero, Matrix.cons_val, Matrix.head_cons]
    <;> ring
  rw [h1, h2, h3, h4]
  all_goals ring_nf <;> simp [Matrix.cons_val_zero, Matrix.cons_val, Matrix.head_cons]
  <;> ring
```

This completes the proof for `partials_helper4`.
